Contributing to SSMSE

Source: CONTRIBUTING.md

Thank you for your interest in contributing to SSMSE! We strive to follow the NMFS Fisheries Toolbox Contribution Guide. We also have included SSMSE-specific contribution information in the Developers page of the SSMSE wiki. Note that these are guidelines, not rules, and we are open to collaborations in other ways that may work better for you. Please feel free to reach out to us by opening an issue in this repository or by emailing the developers at nmfs.stock.synthsis@noaa.gov.

This project and everyone participating in it is governed by the NMFS Fisheries Toolbox Code of Conduct. By participating, you are expected to uphold this code. Instances of abusive, harassing, or otherwise unacceptable behavior may be reported to the community leaders responsible for enforcement at fisheries.toolbox@noaa.gov or to report anonymously, use this form. Note that Kathryn Doering has access to the fisheries.toolbox@noaa and the form. To report violations by Kathryn, instead fill out the FIMS code of conduct form, which goes to Christine Stawitz.

Developed by Kathryn Doering, Nathan Vaughan.
